      "comment": "PAW GUSTO (7) was well backed last start but ran below expectations when seventh (25.02), beaten 18 lengths. Finished second the start before. Some good form is emerging from his last run. Tough to beat if on-song. SHORT STRAW TREV (3) is generally an honest type in the frame at 19 of 42 starts but missed the placings last time when fifth (19.71) over 350m at Healesville. Form at this distance is sound. Looks suited and expected to run well. DR. PATRICK (1) was below best last time at this track (24.31) in a Grade 5, finishing a 2.5 lengths sixth. Already a winner from this draw. Makes strong appeal on best. PANTHER'S WAY (2) gets a chance to redeem an unplaced effort here last start.",
